We are building this PWA in strict phases. Complete each phase fully before 
moving to the next. Each phase should be independently testable. At the end 
of each phase, summarize what was built and flag any decisions made that 
will affect later phases.

---

## PHASE 1 — Project Scaffold & State Foundation
- PWA shell (manifest, service worker, installable)
- App-level state management architecture (choose and justify)
- IndexedDB schema for: contacts, chat threads, settings, summaries
- Basic routing: Chat view, Settings view, Contacts view
- Mobile-first layout skeleton, no functionality yet

Deliverable: Installable PWA shell with navigation and persistent storage ready.

---

## PHASE 2 — Contact Cards & Settings
- Contact card CRUD (create, read, update, delete)
- System instruction field per contact
- LLM configuration per contact (endpoint type, URL, model, API key)
- Global Settings panel:
  - TTS provider + endpoint + speed
  - VAD sensitivity
- Settings persistence to IndexedDB
- Basic settings UI with all controls functional

Deliverable: Fully functional contacts and settings system with persistence.

---

## PHASE 3 — LLM Client Module
- Unified LLM client with adapters for:
  - OpenAI API (streaming chat completions)
  - LETTA streaming voice agent
  - Local inference (Ollama / LM Studio, OpenAI-compatible)
- Streaming response handler
- Vision support detection per endpoint (flag for later use)
- Error handling and retry logic
- Unit-testable in isolation (no UI dependency)

Deliverable: LLM client module that can be imported and tested via console.

---

## PHASE 4 — Basic Chat UI (Push-to-Activate Mode)
- Text thread bubble UI
- Send/receive message flow connected to LLM client
- Contact card selected as active conversation target
- Group thread support (multi-contact threads)
- Rolling context window (configurable size, passed to LLM)
- No audio yet — text only

Deliverable: Functional text chat against any configured LLM endpoint.

---

## PHASE 5 — Audio Pipeline: ASR & VAD
- Microphone access and audio capture
- VAD integration with configurable sensitivity
- Push-to-activate mode:
  - Button hold to record
  - Auto-send after VAD closes
- Live mode:
  - Continuous listening
  - VAD interrupt handling (stop TTS on speech detection)
- ASR result feeds into existing chat send flow

Deliverable: Both ASR modes functional, feeding text into Phase 4 chat.

---

## PHASE 6 — TTS Client Module
- Unified TTS client with adapters for:
  - Kokoro (OpenAI-compatible endpoint)
  - Vibe Voice Realtime (OpenAI-compatible endpoint)
- Streaming audio playback
- Configurable speed
- Interrupt/stop on VAD trigger (hook into Phase 5)
- TTS fires on each assistant response

Deliverable: TTS playback functional in both modes, interruptible.

---

## PHASE 7 — Spectrograph Mouth Visualizer
- Web Audio API analyser node on TTS audio stream
- Spectrograph rendered to Canvas
- Mirrored X and Y to form symmetrical mouth shape
- Rainbow gradient with perlin noise hue drift (avoid mechanical cycling)
- Two size/position states:
  - Small, bottom-anchored (Push-to-Activate mode)
  - Large, centered (Live mode)
- Mouth only animates during TTS playback, idles gracefully

Deliverable: Mouth visualizer running in both modes with correct layout.

---

## PHASE 8 — Live Mode UI
- Full Live Mode layout:
  - Large mouth centered
  - Text bubbles hidden
  - Camera button at bottom
  - Text input bar at bottom
- Smooth mode switching between Push-to-Activate and Live
- All Phase 5–7 audio features verified working in Live Mode layout

Deliverable: Complete Live Mode UI, all audio and visual features integrated.

---

## PHASE 9 — Vision / Image Support
- Camera capture in Live Mode (attach frame on send)
- Manual image attach in Push-to-Activate mode
- Image attached to LLM request payload for vision-capable endpoints
- Graceful degradation: disable/hide image controls for non-vision models
- Preview of attached image before send

Deliverable: Image send functional, vision detection working per endpoint.

---

## PHASE 10 — Memory & Summarizer System
- Rolling context window controls in settings
- Chat Summarizer UI:
  - Message range slider (0–100)
  - Mode selector: Polaroid / Memory
  - Triggers separate inference call outside chat completions
  - Output displayed and optionally saved to contact card notes
- Seed Crystal / New Chat:
  - "New Chat from Current" — runs context through inference, 
    produces ~2000 char seed crystal, seeds new thread
  - "New Chat from Single Response" — new thread from one message
- All summarizer calls use the active contact's LLM config

Deliverable: Full memory and summarizer system functional end to end.

---

## PHASE 11 — Polish, Edge Cases & PWA Hardening
- Offline handling and graceful degradation
- Error states for all network/audio failures
- Loading states and transitions
- Settings validation (test endpoints, show status)
- Accessibility pass (focus management, ARIA where meaningful)
- Performance audit: audio pipeline, canvas render, IndexedDB ops
- Final review of all phases integrated together

Deliverable: Production-ready PWA, all systems integrated and hardened.